        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 2:41PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 240 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from near Skidway Lake to near Rhodes to near
Shepherd. Movement was east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs. Minor damage to
outdoor objects is possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Sanford, Edenville, Bentley, and Pleasant Valley around 245 PM
EDT.
Midland around 250 PM EDT.
Pinconning around 300 PM EDT.
Auburn, Freeland, and Linwood around 315 PM EDT.
Kawkawlin around 325 PM EDT.
Bay City around 330 PM EDT.
Essexville around 335 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Nelson, Mount
Forest, Carrollton, Garfield, Arthur, Crump, Buena Vista Township,
Gera, Poseyville, and Willard.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
